The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, met with Ukrainian President Petro Poroshenko in Munich. They discussed the recent increase in violence in eastern Ukraine and agreed on the urgent need for a comprehensive ceasefire. Pence expressed the U.S.'s support for Ukraine's sovereignty, territorial integrity, and self-determination, emphasizing that the U.S. does not recognize Russia's occupation and attempted annexation of Crimea. He also voiced support for the full implementation of the Minsk agreements, which aim to bring peace to eastern Ukraine. The leaders discussed how the U.S. can assist in negotiations. Pence praised Ukraine's progress on reforms, and both leaders stressed the importance of further reforms to make Ukraine a secure and prosperous European country.